==English==

===Etymology===
Back-formation from [[shoplifter]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to shoplift''' ([[shoplifted]])
{{wikipediapar|shoplifting}}

# to [[steal]] ''something'' from a shop / store during trading hours

====Quotations====
'''transitive'''
*'''2004''': She taught Maddy to sing in Portuguese, to '''shoplift''' mascara, to play a drinking game called Spoons &mdash; Andrew Sean Greer, in ''The New Yorker,'' 17 May 2004

===Intransitive verb===
'''to shoplift''' ([[shoplifted]])

# to [[steal]] from shops / stores during trading hours

====Quotations====
'''instransitive'''
*'''2002''': In other words, New York is a better place to '''shoplift'''. &mdash; ''The New Yorker,'' 25 Nov 2002

====Synonyms====
*[[shop steal]] {{italbrac|Australia}}<!-- rarely "shopsteal" -->

===Related terms===
*[[shoplifter]]
*[[shoplifting]]

